{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_81","type":"agent_message","text":"The execution design is now clear enough to implement. I’m going to add a new `experiment_suite_execution` module that computes a dependency-aware stable schedule from the normalized plan, materializes per-work-item manifest/config snapshots, runs real stage APIs by default, and persists a resume-safe state ledger keyed by `suite_spec_hash` and `work_item_id`.\n\nThe first version will intentionally separate planned suite metadata from realized stage outputs. The planner’s artifact paths are placeholders for later suite packaging, so the runner will keep the normalized plan on disk and record actual produced bundle paths plus stage provenance in a dedicated execution-state file instead of pretending those planned paths are already the source of truth. After that I’ll add a thin script wrapper, a fixture-driven orchestration test with injected stage executors for failure/resume coverage, and the required rationale note."}}
